National Security Advisor Sullivan of the United States, National Security Secretariat Secretary General Akiba Takeo of Japan, and National Security Office Director Cho Tae-yong of South Korea held a trilateral call to discuss the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK). They exchanged views on the recent summit meeting between Russian President Putin and DPRK leader Kim. The three NSAs emphasized the importance of trilateral coordination and reaffirmed their commitment to consult. They also discussed the violation of UN Security Council resolutions, including those voted on by Russia, if the DPRK were to export arms to Russia. Lastly, they reiterated their cooperation in achieving the complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula.